channel.title: INtech
channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from INtech, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: OpenAI hires the team behind Xcode coding assistant Alex Codes
item.description: The team behind Alex Codes, which built a popular tool that let devs use AI models within Apple's development suite Xcode, is joining OpenAI.

item.title: All the Top New Gadgets We Saw at IFA Berlin 2025
item.description: A tennis-playing robot, TCL's gargantuan phone, and a whole bunch of new AI-powered wearables. Here are some of the best gadgets we saw at IFA 2025.

item.title: 7 Best Password Managers (2025), Tested and Reviewed
item.description: Keep your logins locked down with our favorite password management apps for PC, Mac, Android, iPhone, and web browsers.

item.title: Tesla shareholders to vote on investing in Musk’s AI startup xAI
item.description: A shareholder proposal would allow Tesla to invest in Elon Musk's rival AI firm, xAI if approved. Tesla's board didn't recommend one way or another.

item.title: The 29 Best Energy Drinks, Tested and Reviewed (2025)
item.description: The future is here, and it is jacked up on B vitamins, red dye, and taurine. These are the best energy drinks to get from tired to wired.

item.title: The Doomers Who Insist AI Will Kill Us All
item.description: Eliezer Yudkowsky, AI’s prince of doom, explains why computers will kill us and provides an unrealistic plan to stop it.

item.title: Scale AI’s former CTO launches AI agent that could solve big data’s biggest problem
item.description: Isotopes, co-founded by Arun Murthy, launched a sophisticated analytics agent. Arun was one of the creators of Hadoop who later joined Scale AI.

item.title: Tech CEOs Praise Donald Trump at White House Dinner
item.description: At a White House dinner Thursday night, America’s tech executives put on an uncanny display of fealty to Donald Trump.
